George Russell Rogers (20 April 1847 – 14 December 1905) was an English cricketer.  Rogers was a right-handed batsman.  He was born at Brixton, Surrey.
Rogers made his first-class debut for Surrey against Yorkshire in 1870.  He made four further first-class appearances for Surrey in that season, the last of which came against Middlesex.  In his five first-class matches, he scored a total of 34 runs at an average of 3.77, with a high score of 18.He died at Kensington, London on 14 December 1905.
